(a) What is the Composite Pattern?

A composite Pattern iallows you to compose objects in tree structures to represent part whole hierarchies.



(b) Under what conditions would you use a Composite Design Pattern?

Composite pattern is used where we need to treat a group of objects in similar way as a single object. such as a menu
structure that could have other menus or food items


(c) What are the four participants of the Composite Design Pattern?

Client, Component, Leaf and Composite